## Event Horizon Ticket Board

This project uses [Event Horizon](https://github.com/guybnd/event-horizon) as its local-first ticket board, backed by markdown files. Agents interact with tickets exclusively through **MCP tools** ‚Äî never edit `.flux/` or `.flux-store/` files directly.

### Agent Skill Routing ‚Äî REQUIRED

When starting work on a FLUX ticket, **read the Event Horizon orchestrator skill first** (located at `<PROJECT_PATH>/.claude/rules/event-horizon.md`). The skill will route you to the correct phase-specific skill based on ticket status:

| Ticket Status | Load This Skill | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `Grooming`, `Require Input` | `grooming` skill | Planning & requirement clarification |
| `Todo`, `In Progress` | `implementation` skill | Code development & validation |
| Release preparation | `release` skill | Publishing & release orchestration |
| Cross-project mapping | `mapping` skill | Multi-repo documentation |

**For read-only tasks** (explanation, search, discussion) that don't change ticket state, no skill load is required.

---

## Critical Rules ‚Äî Agents MUST Follow

### ‚úã Ticket Persistence Rules

- **NEVER** use `Write` or `Edit` tools on any file in `.flux/` or `.flux-store/` ‚Äî these are engine-managed.
- **NEVER** use `Bash` to write to ticket files (no `echo`, `sed`, `cat >`, etc.).
- **ALWAYS** use the MCP tools below for ticket updates. They handle schema validation and history normalization.

**Why?** Direct file writes bypass engine validation and corrupt ticket history. Changes that only exist in chat are lost ‚Äî the engine is the single source of truth.

### üõÝÔ∏è MCP Tools (Use These For All Ticket Work)

| Tool | Use When |
|---|---|
| `get_ticket` | Reading a ticket (required first step ‚Äî returns digested recent history) |
| `get_session_log` | Reading one prior agent session's full progress log (debugging only) |
| `list_tickets` | Finding tickets by status, priority, assignee, tag |
| `update_ticket` | Changing metadata (title, priority, effort, tags, assignee, body) |
| `change_status` | Moving to a new status (requires comment for `Require Input` / `Ready`) |
| `add_note` | Adding a `type:'comment'` (persists to ticket) or `type:'activity'` (progress update) to history |
| `create_ticket` | Creating a new ticket (pass `parentId` to create a linked subtask) |
| `finish_ticket` | Completing a ticket (atomic: sets link + adds comment + moves to Done) |
| `branch` | `action:'create'` a feature branch, `action:'status'` (ahead/behind vs main), `action:'delete'` (refuses unmerged unless `force:true`) |
| `get_board_config` | Reading board configuration (statuses, tags) |

**Do not use:** chat comments, `add_note` (`type:'activity'`) alone for findings, or direct file edits. Ticket findings must be persisted via `add_note` (`type:'comment'`) or `update_ticket`.

