## Ticket Model

Tickets have these fields (used in MCP tool calls):

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | string | e.g. `FLUX-41` (auto-assigned, never change) |
| `title` | string | Short description |
| `status` | string | Board column: `Grooming`, `Todo`, `In Progress`, `Ready`, `Done`, `Released` |
| `priority` | string | `None`, `Low`, `Medium`, `High`, `Critical` |
| `effort` | string | `None`, `XS`, `S`, `M`, `L`, `XL` |
| `assignee` | string | User name or `unassigned` |
| `tags` | string[] | From board config |
| `body` | markdown | Description & implementation plan |
| `subtasks` | string[] | Child ticket IDs |
| `implementationLink` | string | Commit hash or PR URL (set by `finish_ticket`) |
| `branch` | string | Git branch name (e.g. `flux/FLUX-41-add-field`) |
| `history` | array | Read-only append-only event log (comments, status changes, activity) |

---

## APIs (Fallback Only)

The MCP tools are the primary interface. Use the REST API below **only if MCP tools fail to load** (never for convenience):

- `GET http://localhost:3067/api/tasks` ‚Äî list tickets
- `PUT http://localhost:3067/api/tasks/:id` ‚Äî update ticket (use `appendHistory` for comments)
- `POST http://localhost:3067/api/tasks` ‚Äî create ticket
- `POST http://localhost:3067/api/tasks/:parentId/subtasks` ‚Äî create subtask

---

## End-to-End Checklist

Before marking a ticket `Ready` or `Done`:

- ‚úÖ Ticket read fully ‚Äî relevant docs reviewed
- ‚úÖ Implementation plan posted as a comment (use `add_note`, `type:'comment'`)
- ‚úÖ Status moved at the right time (never skip status transitions)
- ‚úÖ Code changes validated (run tests, start the app, verify behavior)
- ‚úÖ Docs updated (`.docs/` matches new behavior; completion comment says so explicitly)
- ‚úÖ Questions went through `Require Input` status, not only chat
- ‚úÖ Findings persisted via MCP tools, not left in chat or agent memory

